---
// Section 6 — Authority (Manifesto + founder byline)
//
// Layout:
//   - Full-width section heading at top
//   - 2-col grid below: body essay (left, 60%) + pull-quote (right, 40%)
//   - Pull-quote is vertically centered so it lands in the reader's peripheral
//     scan around paragraph 2-3 of the body
//   - Byline (hairline + name + role) sits below the grid, left-aligned
//
// The pull-quote is a verbatim excerpt of the essay's closing line — magazine
// convention. Its job isn't to add new content; it's to amplify the thesis and
// fill the right margin with something functional (the line the skimmer should
// take away), not decorative.
//
// Essay body is set in Instrument Serif at reading size with loose leading and
// natural column measure (no max-w fighting the grid — the column constrains).
//
// Copy: "By 2025, it will clear $37B globally" was future-dated when written.
// Shifted tense since 2025 is now historical. Verify the figure before launch.
---

<section
  id="why"
  class="py-32 md:py-44 px-6 md:px-10 lg:px-16"
  style="background: var(--color-bg);"
>
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <!-- Full-width heading -->
    <h2
      data-reveal
      class="font-serif leading-[1.02] tracking-tight max-w-3xl"
      style="
        color: var(--color-ink);
        font-size: clamp(2rem, 5.2vw, 4.25rem);
      "
    >
      Why this exists.
    </h2>

    <!-- 2-col: essay body (left) + pull-quote (right, vertically centered) -->
    <div
      class="mt-14 md:mt-20 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[3fr_2fr] gap-12 md:gap-16 lg:gap-24"
    >
      <!-- Essay body — serif, generous leading -->
      <div
        data-reveal
        data-reveal-delay="1"
        class="font-serif space-y-6 md:space-y-7 min-w-0"
        style="
          color: var(--color-ink);
          font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 1.6vw, 1.5rem);
          line-height: 1.55;
        "
      >
        <p>
          Creator advertising grows four times faster than total media spend.
          Global spend on the channel now clears $37B. Every number says it's
          one of the most efficient ways for a company to reach a specific
          audience.
        </p>
        <p>
          And yet creator marketing has effectively been reserved for
          enterprise budgets. Not because the creators aren't there — the
          creators are everywhere. Because nobody has built the infrastructure
          to serve anyone below enterprise scale.
        </p>
        <p>
          There's a structural reason. Running a creator campaign end-to-end
          — scoping, sourcing, vetting, outreach, contracts, reporting —
          takes real hours. At enterprise budgets, an agency absorbs those
          hours per client. At mid-market budgets, they can't. So the
          mid-market gets two leftover options: software you have to operate
          yourself, or agencies that don't really want your business.
        </p>
        <p>
          CastWorks fixes the math. Our internal tooling collapses the cost
          of discovery and vetting by orders of magnitude. What's left is the
          work that can't be automated — and that stays human. The result is
          an agency-grade service priced at a commission a real mid-market
          company can sustain.
        </p>
        <p>
          The channel shouldn't be a luxury anymore. That's what we're
          building.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Pull-quote — vertically centered in its column, display serif -->
      <aside
        data-reveal
        data-reveal-delay="2"
        class="md:self-center min-w-0"
      >
        <div
          class="w-12 h-px"
          style="background: var(--color-ink);"
        ></div>
        <blockquote
          class="mt-6 md:mt-8 font-serif leading-[1.08] tracking-tight"
          style="
            color: var(--color-ink);
            font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3.2vw, 3rem);
          "
        >
          The channel shouldn't be a luxury anymore.
        </blockquote>
      </aside>
    </div>

    <!-- Byline: hairline rule + name + role, left-aligned under the grid -->
    <div
      data-reveal
      data-reveal-delay="3"
      class="mt-16 md:mt-20"
    >
      <div class="w-14 h-px" style="background: var(--color-ink);"></div>
      <div class="mt-6 flex items-baseline gap-4 flex-wrap">
        <span
          class="font-serif"
          style="color: var(--color-ink); font-size: clamp(1.125rem, 1.4vw, 1.375rem);"
        >
          Ege Ipek
        </span>
        <span
          class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em]"
          style="color: var(--color-ink-subtle);"
        >
          Founder
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
